@consτ [τ, τ] we're going to make extensive use of the EVM as we explore a few major topics for PTN, sharing our approach with bittensor throughout:

* **Onchain collateral posting**, potentially reducing the registration cost
* **Capacitor feature**, bringing our incentive more in line with miner returns
* **Increased miner capacity / information collection**, potentially opening doors to more miners registered on our platform

We plan to play an active role in public discourse for each of these where possible, as they'll likely be generally useful for a number of timeseries subnets. These tools will of course be _open source_, _easy to integrate_ for other subnets, and we will make ourselves available to help other groups integrate these features.

@ptn・8 as we start development on each, you'll hear from us. Lookout for an upcoming document on collateral, where our quants will outline how we approach pricing and what a potential integration with the EVM might look like. 🎅 almost like Christmas never ended?

